<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
The differences from the subspecies 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Heminothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="capillatus" subSpecies="septentrionalis">septentrionalis Sellnick</taxonomicName>
in Hammer, 1944 (recently redescribed by Sellnick &amp; Forsslund, 1955, p. 519, figs. 21-22) are of minor importance. The species has faint dorsal ridges in the anterior part of the notogaster, which appear to be absent in the subspecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
